|\langle T_{\mu\nu} \rangle| \lesssim \frac{\hbar c}{L_{\text{min}}^4}

Where $L_{\text{min}}$ is the smallest length scale in the problem (e.g., plate separation). This follows from the uncertainty principle and the fact that vacuum energy is concentrated at wavelengths $\sim L$.

Consequence: To achieve stress-energy sufficient for significant spacetime curvature ($\langle T_{00} \rangle \sim c^4/G L^2$), we would need $L \sim L_{\text{Planck}}$, the Planck length. Macroscopic vacuum engineering for gravity control is therefore mathematically impossible within known physics.

